parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of a crash or injury.
symptoms: The ignition switch gets stuck between the "on" and "start" positions
the engine shakes and then shuts off
the vehicle stalls while driving
the engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle will not start
the key fob will not work
the anti-theft light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bags can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the air bags may not deploy or may deploy improperly, leading to metal fragments being released throughout the vehicle.
symptoms: The air bags failed to deploy in a crash
the air bags partially deployed
the air bags deployed improperly
the vehicle was involved in a crash and the air bags did not deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Air Bag Recall Repair Delay
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata air bag recall can cause a safety risk to the vehicle occupants, as the defective air bags may rupture and cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The dealership does not have the parts to repair the vehicle
the dealership is unable to schedule an appointment
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and radiator, and potentially causing an accident or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise from the engine compartment
smoke and fluid leaking from the engine
coolant leaking from the radiator
and the vehicle overheating.
